# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (v1.6.1) using npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the new package and its dependencies

### 2. Modified Files
- **app/layout.tsx**
  - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag after the `<Providers>{children}</Providers>` component
  - Preserves all existing code structure and styling

## Implementation Details
This is an **App Router** project (using `app/` directory), so the Analytics component was added to the root layout file (`app/layout.tsx`) as per Vercel's best practices. The component is placed at the end of the body tag to ensure it loads after the main application content.

## Verification
✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Linter passed for modified files (no new errors introduced)
✅ TypeScript compilation succeeded
✅ All 13 routes generated successfully
✅ Lock files updated correctly

## Notes
- The Analytics component will automatically start tracking page views and web vitals when deployed to Vercel
- No configuration is needed; the component works out of the box
- Analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard once deployed
